==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lignite
<hw>Lig"nite</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧g"n⟦imac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>lignum</ets> wood: cf. F. <ets>lignite</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Mineral coal retaining the texture of the wood
from which it was formed, and burning with an empyreumatic odor. It is
of more recent origin than the anthracite and bituminous coal of the
proper coal series. Called also <altname>brown coal</altname>,
<altname>wood coal</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lignitic</ent>⟦br⟧
